Over the last 5-6 years I have weekly been using Gatwick Express when commuting for work from Gatwick Airport into London. The service has gradually deteriorated which is impacting the journey time and my ability to schedule meetings in London accurately.

i)	The price charged is a premium price for what is turning out to become a mediocre product. What is also a bit perplexing is that customers from Brighton, going through Gatwick Airport on the same train are paying much less – even though they get the same service and more importantly occupy space/seats in the carriages;
ii)	The word ‘Express’ has become an oxymoron, as the train service in the morning is regularly 5-30mins delayed. This is a nuisance and not acceptable for me as a commuter; 
iii)	On top of the delays, there seem to be several gating points where the tickets are checked (3 in total) – and they delay at Victoria Station in front of the turnstiles with a home printed is often very significant (on top of the journey delay!)

The service (product) is not satisfactory and causes a lot of grief and disturbance to the working day.
